			title: "Code Quality & Architectural Improvements: Addressing Technical Debt in Core Components",
			body: "## Summary\n\nAfter conducting a comprehensive analysis of the codebase, I've identified several areas where the code can be improved to enhance maintainability, reduce complexity, and strengthen architectural boundaries. While the codebase is generally **production-quality (8/10)**, there are specific patterns that introduce technical debt and could benefit from refactoring.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Critical: Main.rs God Component Pattern\n\n### Issue\nThe `App` component in `src/main.rs` (~700 lines) violates the Single Responsibility Principle:\n\n- Event routing\n- Render loop orchestration\n- PTY layout calculations\n- Attachment state tracking\n- Liveness polling\n- Terminal event handling\n\nThe presence of `#![allow(clippy::cognitive_complexity)]` (line 168) confirms this is a known issue being suppressed rather than addressed.\n\n### Impact\n- Difficult to test components in isolation\n- High cognitive load for developers modifying the entry point\n- Risk of merge conflicts in the main integration point\n- Changes to one concern (e.g., PTY sizing) risk regressing others (e.g., event routing)\n\n### Recommended Fix\nExtract into focused sub-modules:\n\n```\nsrc/app/\n  mod.rs          # Re-exports and thin integration layer\n  event_router.rs # Event routing and dispatch\n  render_loop.rs  # Frame timing and render orchestration\n  pty_layout.rs   # Terminal size calculations and layout math\n  liveness.rs     # Agent health polling and status updates\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. High: Awkward Context Wrapping Pattern\n\n### Issue\nThe `SharedContext` type uses triple wrapping:\n\n```rust\ntype SharedContext = Option<Arc<std::sync::Mutex<super::AppContext>>>;\n```\n\nThis leads to repetitive unwrapping patterns throughout UI components:\n\n```rust\nif let Some(ctx_arc) = &ctx {\n    let ctx = ctx_arc.lock().unwrap();\n    // ... use ctx\n}\n```\n\n### Impact\n- The `Option` appears unnecessary - context is always available after init\n- Clutters component code with defensive checks for a guaranteed condition\n- Arc<Mutex<_>> is appropriate for sharing, but the Option adds noise\n\n### Recommended Fix\nUse a non-optional shared context or a handle-based approach:\n\n```rust\n// Option 1: Non-optional after initialization\npub struct AppHandle(Arc<Mutex<AppContext>>);\n\n// Option 2: Use tokio/smol's async-aware locks if async context needed\npub type SharedContext = Arc<smol::lock::Mutex<AppContext>>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. High: Blocking I/O in Async Context\n\n### Issue\nIn `src/app_input/mod.rs`, blocking sleep is used in async context:\n\n```rust\nstd::thread::sleep(REMOTE_ATTACH_SETTLE_DELAY);\n```\n\nThis blocks the smol executor thread, preventing other tasks from running.\n\n### Impact\n- UI unresponsiveness during remote agent attachment\n- Wasted executor thread capacity\n- Violates async/await best practices\n\n### Recommended Fix\nReplace with async sleep:\n\n```rust\nsmol::Timer::after(REMOTE_ATTACH_SETTLE_DELAY).await;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Medium: Unbounded Growth of Dead Signatures\n\n### Issue\nIn `src/runtime/manager.rs`:\n\n```rust\ndead_signatures: HashMap<AgentId, LaunchSignature>,\n```\n\nThis map is never cleaned up. If users repeatedly kill and recreate agents, memory grows unbounded.\n\n### Impact\n- Memory leak in long-running sessions\n- No eviction policy for stale signatures\n\n### Recommended Fix\nAdd bounded LRU cache:\n\n```rust\nuse lru::LruCache;\n\nconst MAX_DEAD_SIGNATURES: NonZeroUsize = unsafe { NonZeroUsize::new_unchecked(100) };\n\ndead_signatures: LruCache<AgentId, LaunchSignature>,\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Medium: Layout Constant Duplication\n\n### Issue\nMagic numbers are duplicated between `main.rs` and UI components:\n\n```rust\n// main.rs\nconst LEFT_COL_WIDTH: u16 = 22;\n\n// dashboard.rs (implicitly assumes this width)\n// sidebar.rs (hardcodes related values)\n```\n\n### Impact\n- Single source of truth violation\n- Changing layout requires coordinated edits across files\n- Risk of inconsistency\n\n### Recommended Fix\nCreate a `layout.rs` module with shared constants:\n\n```rust\n// src/ui/layout.rs\npub const SIDEBAR_WIDTH: u16 = 22;\npub cons",
