			number: 25,
			title: "Consistent crash on my system due to UTF-8 BOM encoding in reliquified_ars_nouveau.mixins.json",
			body: "Hi there! First of all, thank you for this great mod!\n\nI have been experiencing a crash on my system since version 0.8.0 up to the latest version. The crash log points to `reliquified_ars_nouveau.mixins.json`, and I found that the root cause is that this file is saved with **UTF-8 BOM** encoding.\n\nAfter converting the file to **UTF-8 without BOM**, the crash stopped completely.\n\nThis may not reproduce on your end, since different systems or Git configurations may handle the BOM differently. But on my machine it is **consistently reproducible**, and switching to UTF-8 without BOM fixes it every time.\n\n**Steps to reproduce:**\n- Launch the game with the mod installed — the crash happens every time on my system.\n\n**Root cause:**\n- The file `reliquified_ars_nouveau.mixins.json` uses UTF-8 with BOM, which some JSON parsers (especially Minecraft's) may not handle correctly, causing parse failures.\n\n**Suggested fix:**\n- Re-save `reliquified_ars_nouveau.mixins.json` (and potentially other `.json` files) with UTF-8 encoding **without BOM**.\n\nI hope this helps! Let me know if you need any more information.",
