			title: "Template Strings reformatted to newlines with oxc minify enabled.",
			body: "### Describe the bug\n\nI've taken ages trying to figure this out and I presume is a bug or lacking documentation for the oxc minify transformation. \n\nA template literal string with new lines. Is not being compressed when compress is enabled. The strings in question are vertex and fragment shaders. That should retain \\n to output new lines in the shader program but compress. I am not sure how to convert and transform properly. \n\nSo even the second example with a string like `TEST \\n TEST` is being pretty formatted. I am pre transforming the strings. When minify is disabled the string is compressed. \n\n### Reproduction\n\nna\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nStrings in a module\n\n```js\nexport const FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM = `TEST\nTEST\nTEST\nTEST\n`;\n\nexport const FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM2 = `TEST \\n TEST \\n TEST \\n TEST`;\n```\n\n\nBuild config\n\n```\nbuild: {\n      minify: 'oxc', \n      outDir: 'build',\n      sourcemap: false,\n      emptyOutDir: false,\n      lib: {\n        entry: ['./index.ts'],\n        fileName: (format, entryName) => {\n          return `index.js`;\n        },\n        formats: ['es'],\n      },\n      rolldownOptions: {\n  \n        output: {\n         \n          codeSplitting: false,\n          comments: false,\n       \n          minify: {\n            mangle: false,\n            compress: true\n          }\n        },\n      },\n```\n\nOutput\n\n```\nvar FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM=`TEST\nTEST\nTEST\nTEST\n`,FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM2=`TEST \n TEST \n TEST \n TEST\n`;export{FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM,FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM2};\n```\n\n\nOutput without minify and transforming new lines in a plugin. \n\n```\nvar FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM = \"TEST\\nTEST\\nTEST\\nTEST\";\nvar FRAGMENT_TRANSFORM2 = \"TEST \\n TEST \\n TEST \\n TEST\";\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n    OS: Linux 6.6 Debian GNU/Linux 13 (trixie) 13 (trixie)\n    CPU: \n    Memory: 7.06 GB / 7.71 GB\n    Container: Yes\n    Shell: 5.2.37 - /bin/bash\n  Binaries:\n    Node: 26.2.0 - .nvm/versions/node/v26.2.0/bin/node\n    npm: 11.16.0 - .nvm/versions/node/v26.2.0/bin/npm\n    bun: 1.3.13 - .bun/bin/bun\n  npmPackages:\n    vite: ^8.0.16 => 8.0.16\n```\n\n### Used Package Manager\n\nnpm\n\n### Logs\n\n_No response_\n\n### Validations\n\n- [x] Follow our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/vitejs/vite/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\n- [x] Read the [Contributing Guidelines](https://github.com/vitejs/vite/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n- [x] Read the [docs](https://vite.dev/guide).\n- [x] Check that there isn't [already an issue](https://github.com/vitejs/vite/issues) that reports the same bug to avoid creating a duplicate.\n- [x] Make sure this is a Vite issue and not a framework-specific issue. For example, if it's a Vue SFC related bug, it should likely be reported to [vuejs/core](https://github.com/vuejs/core) instead.\n- [x] Check that this is a concrete bug. For Q&A open a [GitHub Discussion](https://github.com/vitejs/vite/discussions) or join our [Discord Chat Server](https://chat.vite.dev/).\n- [x] The provided reproduction is a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) of the bug.",
